  <brief_title>Efficacy and Safety of Aprotinin on Transfusion Requirements in Patients Undergoing Radical or Total Cystectomy</brief_title>
  <official_title>A Multi-center, Randomized, Double Blind, Placebo Controlled Study to Investigate the Efficacy and Safety of Aprotinin on Transfusion Requirements in Patients With Bladder Cancer Undergoing Radical or Total Cystectomy.</official_title>
  <sponsors>
    <lead_sponsor>
      <agency>Bayer</agency>
      <agency_class>Industry</agency_class>
    </lead_sponsor>
  </sponsors>
  <source>Bayer</source>
  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to assess if aprotinin (BAYA0128), given intravenously during
      your surgery, is safe and can help reduce the need for a blood transfusion during bladder
      surgery.
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
